results.description:
A Bouquet.
The taste for overcrowded flower and fruit still lifes became outmoded at the end of the 18th century. Henri√´tte Geertruida Knip responded to this change, painting watercolours like this one with only a few kinds of blossoms and, moreover, omitting the vase. Her elegant flower pieces were extremely popular. One of her watercolours even won a silver medal in Paris in 1819.
